                        "displayName": "Will Jones",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Marven. What OS are you on and how did you install Python?\r\n\r\nIt looks like you are specifying the path the executable and that is working. However, it looks like it's missing numpy ({{pip install numpy}}) and the Python development libraries (usually called {{python-devel}} or {{python-dev}} in most linux package managers). If you install both of those that should fix that error.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=willjones127",
                        "name": "willjones127",
                        "key": "willjones127",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34058",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34058",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34058",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34058"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Will Jones",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "created": "2022-01-31T22:42:09.838+0000",
                    "updated": "2022-01-31T22:42:09.838+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13424988/comment/17485200",
                    "id": "17485200",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mgiessing",
                        "name": "mgiessing",
                        "key": "JIRAUSER284243",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Marvin Giessing",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Will,\r\n\r\nI'm using manylinux2014_ppc64le images and therefore python is already installed, I did also install python3-devel as well as numpy and all the other dependencies\r\n\r\nI fixed the error by setting a static library file into the directories like this:\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n{code:java}\r\nexport VERSIONS=\"cp37-cp37m cp38-cp38 cp39-cp39\"\r\nfor ver in ${VERSIONS}\r\ndo\r\n  PYTHON_INTERPRETER=/opt/python/${ver}/bin/python\r\n \u00a0CPYTHON_PATH=/opt/python/${ver}\r\n  py_libname=$(${PYTHON_INTERPRETER} -c \"import sysconfig; print(sysconfig.get_config_var('LDLIBRARY'))\")\r\n  touch ${CPYTHON_PATH}/lib/${py_libname}\r\ndone{code}\r\nSeems like the docker image has no python libs which then throws errors on cmake\r\n\r\n\u00a0\r\n\r\n--> [https://github.com/pypa/manylinux/issues/484]",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=mgiessing",
                        "name": "mgiessing",
                        "key": "JIRAUSER284243",
                        "avatarUrls": {
